quran[37]{c,v,t}:
  56,75,I do swear by the positions of the stars –
  56,76,"and this is indeed a great oath, if only you knew –"
  56,77,that this is indeed a noble Qur’an
  56,78,in a well-preserved Record
  56,79,"that none can touch except the purified [angels] –"
  56,80,a revelation from the Lord of the worlds
  56,81,Do you take this discourse lightly
  56,82,"and instead [of thanking Allah] for the provision you are given, you show ingratitude"
  56,83,"Then why [you are helpless] when the soul reaches the throat"
  56,84,while you are looking on
  56,85,"when We are closer to him than you, but you do not see"
  56,86,"If you are not subject to retribution, then why do you not"
  56,87,"bring that [soul] back, if you are truthful"
  56,88,If that dying person is one of those who will be brought near to Allah
  56,89,"then [he will have] comfort, fragrance, and Garden of Bliss"
  56,90,If he is one of the people of the right
  56,91,"[He will be told], “Peace be to you, for being one of the people of the right.”"
  56,92,But if he is one of the misguided deniers
  56,93,then he will be welcomed with scalding water
  56,94,and he will burn in Blazing Fire
  56,95,This is indeed the absolute truth
  56,96,"So glorify the name of your Lord, the Most Great"
  57,1,"All that is in the heavens and earth glorifies Allah, for He is the All-Mighty, the All-Wise"
  57,2,"To Him belongs the dominion of the heavens and earth; He gives life and causes death, and He is Most Capable of all things"
  57,3,"He is the First and the Last, the Manifest and the Hidden, and He is All-Knowing of everything"
  57,4,"It is He Who created the heavens and earth in six days, and then rose over the Throne. He knows all that goes into the earth and all that comes out of it, and all that descends from the heaven and all that ascends to it. He is with you wherever you are, and Allah is All-Seeing of what you do"
  57,5,"To Him belongs the dominion of the heavens and earth, and to Allah will return all matters"
  57,6,"He causes the night to merge into the day and the day to merge into the night, and He is All-Knowing of what is in the hearts"
  57,7,"Believe in Allah and His Messenger, and spend [in Allah’s cause] out of what He has entrusted you with. For those among you who believe and spend, there will be a great reward"
  57,8,"Why is it that you do not believe in Allah when the Messenger is calling you to believe in your Lord, and He has already taken a covenant from you, if you will ever believe"
  57,9,"It is He Who sends down clear verses to His slave to bring you out of the depths of darkness into the light. Indeed, Allah is Ever Gracious and Most Merciful to you"
  57,10,"Why is it that you do not spend in the cause of Allah, when Allah alone will inherit the heavens and earth? Those of you who spent and fought before the conquest [of Mecca and those who did not] are not equal. They are much greater in rank than those who spent and fought afterwards. Yet Allah has promised each a fine reward, and Allah is All-Aware of what you do"
  57,11,"Who is there to lend Allah a goodly loan, so He will multiply it for him, and for him there will be a generous reward"
  57,12,"[Remember] the Day when you will see the believing men and women, with their light streaming ahead of them and on their right. [They will be told], “Glad tidings for you Today: gardens under which rivers flow, abiding therein forever.” That is the supreme triumph"
  57,13,"On that Day the hypocrite men and women will say to those who believe, “Wait for us, so that we may have some of your light.” It will be said, “Go back and seek light elsewhere.” Then a wall will be placed between them, which will have a gate, on the inside of which there will be mercy and on the outside there will be punishment"
  57,14,"The hypocrites will call out to the believers, “Were we not with you?” They will say, “Yes, but you allowed yourselves to succumb to temptations, you awaited [some misfortune to befall us], you doubted, and you were deceived by false hopes, until Allah’s decree came to pass. Thus the deceiver [Satan] deceived you concerning Allah"
  57,15,So this Day no ransom will be accepted from you or from the disbelievers. Your abode is the Fire; it is a fitting place for you – what a wretched destination!”